Description: Fragment of handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay near fine brown. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Pencil '57?'. Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 134, 3 or 181, 31. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0321.14.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1208)
